==English==
===Etymology===
From Old French ''[[Antarctique]]'', from Latin ''[[Antarcticus]]'', from Greek ''[[antarktikos]]'', from ''[[ant-]]'' (from ''[[anti-]]'' "opposite") + ''[[arktos]]'' "[[Great Bear]]" + ''[[-ikos]]''

===Pronunciation===
* ''[[RP]]:''
** {{IPA|/ænˈtɑːktɪk/}}

===Adjective===
'''Antarctic'''
# {{obsolete}} [[southern|Southern]].
# Of, from, or pertaining to [[Antarctica]] and the south [[polar]] regions.
# (''figurative'') [[opposite|Opposite]], [[contradictory]].

====Derived terms====
* [[Antarctic Ocean]]
* [[Antarctic Circle]]

